<Content>Worst Hotel Ever This was the absolute WORST hotel ever. I booked the room through Orbitz, and read reviews here. After reading the reviews I thought I was safe. Big mistake. It started with the shuttle from the airport. I was the only passenger in the van and the driver stopped to pick up her friend. I then had to listen to their ghetto talk all the way to the hotel. When I got there I was told they couldn't find my reservation. They explained that the computer had lost all of the reservations. After 15 minutes it miraculously reappeared. I think the girl behind the counter was just totally incompetant. Then I was assigned my room, and I went up to change. I had plans to meet friends for dinner in 20 minutes so I didn't even have time to shower. When I came back at midnight I was totally exhausted and went right to bed. I got up in the morning and upon entering the shower I realized there was a dirty rag hanging on the shower head. I figured the maid had forgotten to take it with her. Five minutes later the maid comes in and explains that the room was supposed to be vacant. That it was never cleaned the day before. I started to look around, and to my absolute horror I noticed trash in the can, towels missing on the shelf, and the toilet paper was not folded all nice like they do. The house keeping supervisor explained that the room had indeed not been cleaned and that whoever checked me in put me in a dirty room. I was livid. The front desk staff told me there was nothing they could do to compensate me because I had paid through Orbitz. Then they tried to say it was somehow my fault because I didn't inspect the room when I checked in. That it was my fault I had slept in dirty sheets. This story is long enough so I will just add one more thing. The shuttle driver on the way back to the airport dropped me off five miles form the hotel and nowhere near the airport, because he was going somewhere else first and didn't want to drive all the way back to the airport. He radioed for another shuttle to come and git this dude from shugga baybees, he need to go to da a-pote and then left me in a parking lot in the blaring sun. I am mortified at the though of anyone else staying at this hotel. Please Beware. 
